1. Bukvalno ne mogu da verujem koliko si brzo vozio. (Literally, I can't believe how fast you were driving.)
2. Nije mi jasno kako se to bukvalno desilo. (I don't understand how that literally happened.)
3. Bukvalno me je iznenadila ta vest. (That news literally surprised me.)
4. Mogu bukvalno da osetim miris tvoje kafe. (I can literally smell your coffee.)
5. Bukvalno sam jurio ceo dan. (I was literally rushing all day.)
6. Sve vreme sam bukvalno mislio na tebe. (I was literally thinking about you the whole time.)
7. Bukvalno sam progutao knedlu kada sam video tu sliku. (I literally swallowed a lump in my throat when I saw that picture.)
8. Bukvalno se hvatam za slamku da bih pre≈æiveo ovaj dan. (I'm literally clinging to a straw to survive this day.)

Note: In Serbian, the word "bukvalno" is used similarly to the English word "literally." It can be used to emphasize the exactness or accuracy of something, or to express the speaker's surprise, disbelief, or strong emotions.